  <h2>Work</h2>

  <div class="role">
    <h3>
      <a href="https://octopus.energy">Octopus Energy</a> (December 2015 -
      Present)
    </h3>
    <p><strong>Global Director of Engineering</strong></p>
    <p>
      Having been at Octopus Energy since its formation in 2015, I built and
      lead the Global Engineering team - overseeing its growth and development,
      crafting sites and internal tools, building new products and campaigns,
      and expanding into other countries.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our aim is to combat climate change, use technology to build a better
      standard of energy supplier, and make renewable energy more affordable for
      everyone. The teams feature Front-end and Back-end web development,
      Mobile, Design, Product, and Data Visualisation. Over these years, I have
      learned how to manage across disciplines, timezones, and various team
      sizes, and discovered my love for it as a job.
    </p>
    <p>
      In May 2020, Octopus Energy became the 15th UK tech
      <strong>‚Äúunicorn‚Äù</strong> after achieving a valuation of
      <a
        href="https://octopus.energy/blog/octopus-energy-achieves-unicorn-status-investment-origin-energy/"
        >over &pound;1 billion</a
      >. At the time of writing, Octopus Energy Group is valued at over $9bn.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong
        >Stack: React, NextJS, GraphQL, Apollo, Jest, React Testing Library,
