<div class="section">
  <h2>Writing</h2>

  <div class="project">
    <h3>
      <a href="https://learna11y.com"
        >Practical Web Accessibility (Second Edition)</a
      >
    </h3>
    <p>
      The revamped and updated second edition of my first book abotu web
      accessibility. You'll be guided through a broad range of disabilities and
      access needs, understand the ways these users typically engage with the
      web, the barriers they often face, and practical advice on how your
      websites and content can be compliant, but more than that, inclusive and
      enjoyable.
    </p>
    <p>It's suitable for anyone regardless of role or experience.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="project">
    <h3>
      <a
        href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Practical-Web-Inclusion-Accessibility-Comprehensive/dp/1484254511/"
        >Practical Web Inclusion and Accessibility</a
      >
    </h3>
    <p>
      My first book, published with <a href="https://apress.com">Apress</a> in
      2020, about web accessibility. It topped the Amazon technology charts.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="project">
    <h3>
      <a href="static/documents/articles/accessibility-webdesigner272.pdf"
        >Accessibility: a web for all</a
      >
    </h3>
    <p><strong>Web Designer Magazine</strong> (Issue 272)</p>
    <p>
      A feature for a print magazine talking about designing and developing for
      general web accessibility, and helping those with specific disabilities.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="project">
    <h3><a href="/blog">Personal blog</a></h3>
    <p>
      A more personal space for my writing. Typically includes thoughts on
      management, accessibility, productivity, and how me, my team, and Octopus
      Energy handle things.
    </p>
  </div>
